instruction: Summarize a book review in 100 words or less.
input: The book "The Catcher in the Rye" is written by J. D. Salinger.
output: The Catcher in the Rye is one of J. D. Salinger’s best-known works. It follows the teenage protagonist, Holden Caulfield, in his struggles to make sense of the world around him and his struggle to live a meaningful life. Holden's story is told with tremendous wit and insight, and it resonates with readers of all ages. The book is a timeless classic and one of the greatest coming-of-age stories ever written.
